description: I became licensed in 2010 after an extensive history in luxury sales & executive management. description: More about Lisa Meet Lisa Harris - one of Omaha’s top producers. Consistently ranked in the top 12% of all Berkshire Hathaway Home Services realtors in the US, Lisa has developed a keen aptitude stemming  from her sincere interest, knowledge and experience in the industry. Now, a longtime resident of the Omaha area and having raised her two daughters here, Lisa has gained a full understanding of the diverse needs of families in the community. Even with the sales, training and awards, Lisa simply wants you to enjoy the real estate process and have you win in the end. She has a true passion for exceeding your expectations from the moment you begin working together.

description: My name is Lynette Dole a Realtor at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate and proud member of Team O As a graduate of Randall School of Real Estate and a licensed realtor since 2012, I pride myself on providing exceptional service that goes above and beyond for my clients. Prior to embarking on my career in real estate, I owned a successful gift basket business for 13 years. My experience as a business owner has instilled in me a strong work ethic, attention to detail, and the ability to work well under pressure. I am licensed in Nebraska and Iowa, and have a wealth of knowledge about the local real estate market, which I leverage to help both buyers and sellers make informed decisions. My passion for real estate, coupled with my commitment to delivering the best possible results, has earned me a reputation as a dedicated and trustworthy realtor. When I'm not working, you can find me cheering on the Kansas City Chiefs, playing games, boating, fishing, or spending time with my family and friends. I am also an active member of MOBA, Women's Council of Realtors, OABR, and SWIAR. Through these organizations, I have gained valuable insights and strengthened my network, which ultimately benefits my clients. I have earned several designations, including Graduate Realtor Institute (GRI), Residential Investment Specialist (RIS) , Military Relocation Professional (MRP), Pricing Strategy Advisor (PSA) and Certified New Construction Specialist (CNCS), which demonstrate my commitment to ongoing education and professional development. These designations have equipped me with the tools and knowledge to offer my clients cutting-edge insights and expertise, delivering the best possible results. If you're looking for a realtor who is passionate, knowledgeable, and dedicated to helping you achieve your real estate goals, look no further.  I am committed to providing you with an unparalleled level of service, and I look forward to working with you.

description: Meet Ashima Energetic. Passionate. Knowledgeable. ‘Open, honest communication is the best foundation for any relationship, but remember that at the end of the day it’s not what you say or what you do, but how you make people feel that matters the most.” - Tony Hsieh, CEO of Zappos Ashima Choudhary loves working with people.  She brings her creativity, enthusiasm and sharp attention to detail to help buyers search for their new house that matches their needs and help sellers get the most value for their home.  Ashima is known for her integrity and sincerity in all her dealings. “I will listen to you!” Buying and selling can oftentimes be a stressful process but it does not need to be.  Ashima is an excellent communicator and she will spend as much time as you need to explain each part of the process in detail. She will work hard to lower your stress to make the experience as enjoyable as possible. “I am not #1, but you are my #1 priority!” Ashima will be an advocate for you to help you save time and money.  She has decades of experience working for her clients at her prior enterprises - whether it be in helping with their complicated banking needs or be as simple as helping them board a flight.  She was rated top customer service agent for her ability to listen to her clients and solve their problems. “I believe that building relationships is far more important than business” Ashima Choudhary was born and raised in India to a military family.  She moved to Omaha from California in 2008 and has not looked back.  She loves Omaha’s Midwest family-oriented culture and its friendly people. When Ashima is not helping client, she is busy shuttling her two boys to their activities and keeping her husband out of trouble!  She loves to try new restaurants and cuisines.  She also loves to travel both within our wonderful country and internationally.  She is an avid dancer and loves to work out. Please call me or email me if you have any real estate related questions - even if you are not ready to buy or sell today. "Strive not to be a success, but rather to be of value." - Albert Einstein Your Referral is the Best Compliment I can Earn !!!

description: I believe every real estate transaction should be simplified and transparent, backed with expertise and support, and driven by your specific goals and dreams. I provide no-strings-attached consultations and complimentary home valuations to any potential client. Whether you're buying your first home or your 5th, whether you are selling, downsizing, investing, or anything in between, I prioritize education on the process, market updates and standards, valuation, and strategy. Real estate transactions are complex and involve several moving parts, and it's my job to stand by you every step of the way and help navigate you to the future you are dreaming of. Ever since I was a child, I've loved looking at houses, and I would dream about what my perfect house would look like. I have always been fascinated with architectural history and design; a fascination which later led me to study architectural drafting and interior design at The New York Institute of Art and Design. While designing unique interiors for each client, it became clear to me then that a house is not a home without someone to love it, and I began to pursue a life in real estate. Outside of my love of real estate and design, I am also passionate about painting, volunteering, playing music, and stargazing. Call me for a consultation or free home valuation today!

description: Cindy Cawley is a full-time real estate agent with 28 years of experience selling homes and condominiums in the luxury market in Omaha, Nebraska. Born and raised in Omaha, she graduated from Creighton University with a teaching degree. She has helped hundreds of homeowners buy and sell their homes in Omaha and all surrounding areas -- executive homes, condominiums, lake homes, acreages, downtown and midtown condos and townhouses, villas, first-time homeowners, and those new to the Omaha area. Specilizing in District 66/Westside, Regency, Rockbrook,  Linden Estates, The Sanctuary, The Ridges, Five Fountains, Baywood, Fairacres, Dundee, Happy Hollow Country Club area, Aksarben, and Memorial Park and downton Omaha, Elkhorn, Millard, Bennington, and Lincoln homes. As a former teacher, Cindy has a vast knowledge of the private and public school systems in the Omaha area. When asked why she chose real estate as a career, she always mentions her job is teaching clients the process of buying and selling a home. Cindy has helped countless physicians and their families relocating to area hospitals / medical centers. In addition to being a relocation specialist, her passion for having happy customers has always been her top priority. She possesses the qualities buyers and sellers want with their agent. Listening closely to her clients and matching their wants and needs has resulted in Cindy Cawley being one of the city's top real estate agents year after year.  Many of her clients are repeat customers who have trusted Cindy's expertise with their personal homes and continue to recommend her to fellow co-workers and extended family. No doubt, Cindy has the work ethic and drive to put her clients first when marketing their home or seaching for a home that checks all the boxes! Experience counts with the largest investment most people make in a lifetime. Cindy Cawley's vast knowledge ensures your best interests are represented when selling or buying a home. Call Cindy today for your real estate needs in Omaha!

description: MEET CHAPIN Welcome and thanks for finding me here! I am a lifelong Omaha resident. I grew up in midtown and I have always loved old homes and tree lined streets.I have watched Omaha grown over the decades and my comprehensive knowledge of the city can be put to work for you. After graduating from Creighton University in 2006 with a BSBA in Marketing my real estate career started in property management. I worked for a national real estate investment trust (REIT). I enjoyed working in the real estate industry and received my sales licence in 2010. I learned quickly that just like every home, every real estate transaction is different. I understand that this industry requires staying current in market trends, good communication and above all else honesty. I pride myself on protecting my clients interests with integrity and honesty. Real estate is not my only passion. Since receiving my license I married my best friend and we now have two daughters. Our four legged-fur kid is a Golden Retriever, Pearl. When I am not selling real estate or attending kid activites, my husband and I love to travel. I also enjoy spending time with my family, entertaining friends and being active. What can you expect when working with me? My clients work directly with me and we walk through the process of buying and/or selling a home together. The real estate market can be challenging but with proactive problem solving we can navigate it together. In my opinion, communication is key and is the foundation to success. A home is the biggest investment most of us will ever make. I hope that when it is time for you to make your dream come true you will allow me to help you see it through.

description: Starting in the Real Estate business in 2002, I have the confidence, knowledge and expertise to help you with any of your Residential Real Estate needs.  I love helping every client find a home that perfectly fits their needs, whether it's buying an existing home or building a brand new one.  Born and raised in South Omaha, Nebraska,  As a child, we always took Sunday drives and my Dad drove us home "the long way", so little did I know I was learning how to take every back road and alley in town.  By the time I was 16, I was driving Omaha knowing exactly where I was going and how to take a detour to get there faster if I needed to. What I love about Omaha, is we are your Little Big Town.  Omaha, Nebraska maintains that “small town” feeling, with some big city amenities. Enjoy the World Famous, Omaha Henry Doorly Zoo, catch a College World Series Baseball game at Charles Schwab Field in June, People watch in the Old Market while attending the Summer Arts Festival and Farmers Markets, visit the newest & best family friendly downtown, the Gene Leahy Mall & River Waterfront parks.   Don't forget to entice your appetite with some of the best eats around, like the Reuben Sandwich created right here in Omaha.  Walk the 3000 sq. ft. floating bridge over the Missouri River from downtown Omaha to Council Bluffs, Iowa.  (yes, it's walkable, you can place one foot in Nebraska & one foot in Iowa at the same time!). My main goal for every client, let me handle the complex details, so it's an easy transition from home to home for you. If you're selling, buying, investing or building, I'm happy to help! description: Your Trusted Realtor and Interior Designer Are you feeling overwhelmed by the complexities of buying or selling a home? Look no further! I'm Jenna Friesen, a seasoned realtor and experienced interior designer, here to simplify the process for you. With a deep understanding of the Omaha real estate market, I specialize in helping clients navigate their unique circumstances and find their ideal homes. As a recipient of the prestigious 2021 President's Circle award and a nominee for New Ambassador of the Year in 2023, my dedication to excellence is evident. I take pride in the many 5-star reviews from satisfied clients, who have entrusted me with their real estate journeys. Whether you're looking to downsize, upgrade, relocate within the town, or venture beyond state lines, I will guide you toward the best options for you and your family. With a track record of success, including the 2022 Leading Edge Society award from BHHS and a nomination for Rookie of the Year in 2020, I have helped numerous families turn their dreams of homeownership into reality. My expertise in both real estate and interior design ensures that you'll receive comprehensive guidance and personalized solutions every step of the way. Let's work together to make your next move a seamless and fulfilling experience. Contact me today, and let's embark on this exciting journey of finding your perfect home. ____________________________________ Omaha is a thriving city that combines a rich history with modern amenities and a strong economy. With its affordable housing options, steady job growth, and a friendly community, Omaha has become an attractive destination for investors seeking long-term returns. Whether you're interested in residential or commercial properties, Omaha has a diverse range of options to suit your investment strategy. As a local real estate agent, I have an in-depth understanding of the Omaha market, keeping up with the latest trends and developments. I can guide you through the entire investment process, from finding properties with excellent potential to negotiating favorable deals. My goal is to ensure you make informed decisions and maximize your returns. In addition to my expertise in real estate, I also offer interior designing services. Whether you're looking to enhance the aesthetic appeal of your investment property or want to stage it for sale, I can help you create a visually stunning and functional space. With my eye for design and knowledge of current trends, I can transform your property into a standout investment. Investing in Omaha real estate is a smart choice due to the city's steady growth, strong rental demand, and favorable economic conditions. Let me, Jenna Friesen, be your trusted partner in this exciting journey. Together, we can navigate the Omaha market, find lucrative opportunities, and create spaces that attract both tenants and buyers.

description: In the Omaha metro area, Fred Tichauer is highly regarded for his unparalleled knowledge of residential real estate investment. Fred teaches continuing education classed approved by the Nebraska Real Estate Commission. With half a century of success as an investor, Fred understands the ins and outs of the investment niche market form the perspectives of the investor and agent. His proven system will push you to achieve your financial objectives. He believes there's nothing better than a real estate investment portfolio consisting of residential properties located in "family-friendly" neighborhoods. He is certain that anyone who is creditworthy and is willing to work hard can achieve the financial freedom they deserve.

description: Mike is the Commercial Division Manager for the Berkshire Hathaway HS | Ambassador Real Estate company, serving the Omaha Metro, Nebraska and Iowa. With a background in sales, banking, and real estate, Mike is 'client-centric', - a 'matchmaker' for his clients and their real estate needs. Includes listing and selling brokerage, landlord AND tenant rep leasing, revitalization and/or re-purposing existing buildings, and new developments. Our Commercial Division has a very strong background and experience in all aspect of new development, construction management, project management, asset management, critical analyis of a building and/or an entire project for analyzing the project feasibility and potential profitability. Mike currently serves as Vice-Chair of the MRCIE (Midlands Regional Commercial Information Exchange) serving Nebraska and Iowa, beginning May1, 2017. Mike is a member of Governmental Affairs Committee for the Omaha Area Board of Realtors. Historically, Mike has been in consultative selling all of his life. Mike invested 12 years in the life insurance and employee benefits business, including financial planning, estate planning, and employee benefit planning, for the medium size business owners and high income earners. Mike earned his professional designation as a CLU in 1976 from The American College in Bryn Mawr, PA, which has proved time and again to be valuable background to assist his real estate clients. An opportunity arose to enter the banking business in a small town bank, where Mike learned all facets of banking, from the teller to the regulatory filings to agriculture, consumer, and commercial business lending. These two careers had a huge impact and fabulous background training for a career in real estate since 1981. Back in Omaha since 2000, Mike has increased his commercial sales, real estate investment analysis skills, and developement and asset management skills with hands-on involvement and counseling a myriad of diffferent experience level of investors and owner/users of commercial real estate. Mike works by referral. If you or your friends and/or associates have a project you are interested in, please feel free to contact Mike to see if we - The Project, Mike - or one of our Team, and You, are a 'Match'!! We love to help make a project come to life and become a success.

description: Steve is recognized leader in the local and national business arena, with a three-decade plus focus in real estate, financial services and banking. Steve currently serves as a Merger and Acquisitions Specialist in the Commercial Division of Berkshire Hathaway HS | Ambassador Real Estate.  In this role, he assists businesses wishing to transition in facilitating a buyer, works to find the appropriate structure for the transaction and assists in the transfer of Real Estate involved.  He has been affiliated with Berkshire Hathaway HS | Ambassador Real Estate since August of 2020. He also served in a consulting role for BHHSAMB in 2016 and 2017. Prior to this, Steve served as the Managing Director for the Private Banking Division of Mutual of Omaha Bank.  He served in this role in Omaha and Scottsdale from March 2018 until the bank was acquired by CIT Bank in August 2020. Steve lived in Denver Colorado in 2017, on a consulting assignment for a former high profile Wall Street CEO, rationalizing an expansion plan into Denver from the New York City operation. From 2010 to 2016, he served as President and Chairman of Tributary Mutual Funds, and as President of Tributary Capital Management LLC.  Steve re-engineered a declining investment management platform used primarily by the trust department of a community bank into a nationally known boutique asset manager utilized by industry heavyweights JP Morgan, UBS, Wells Fargo, Envestnet, PNC, Charles Schwab and Fidelity. During this time, Steve also served as President of Tributary Capital Management LLC.  In his tenure as leader, he grew the assets in the Flagship Small Cap strategy from $60 million in 2010 to over $1 billion in 2016.  The growth was almost exclusively sourced through channels outside of the parent banking organization.  The strategy and the firm have received multiple industry awards and accolades over Steve’s tenure, including the US News and World Report, Mutual Fund Observer, the Wall Street Journal and Pensions and Investments. Tributary was also awarded the Envestnet Small Cap SMA Manager of the year in 2016. Steve also served as Chief Compliance Officer for Tributary, managed the P&L, had sales and marketing responsibilities, key account client responsibilities as well as quarterly client calls on key portfolio and market related issues. Prior to his tenure at Tributary, Steve served for over a decade as Chief Investment Officer for Tributary’s parent, First National Bank of Omaha. He took on this role at a time when the bank was experiencing significant asset redemptions.  Over the ensuing decade, Steve guided the organization through a period of mass transformation. Steve’s previous experience includes J. Stephan Co. a third-party institutional asset management marketing firm, representing Thomson Horstmann and Bryant in Saddle Brook New Jersey, and Lazard London International, London England. Steve also held roles with Waddell and Reed Asset Management, Shawnee Mission Kansas and Parametric Portfolio Associates, Seattle Washington.  He began his financial services career as an account executive with Smith Barney Harris Upham in 1984 where he was a member of the constellation club, awarded annually to the top 15 rookie brokers across the country.  He also served as the local specialist in evaluating all private placement and publicly traded real estate transactions. He is a 1983 graduate of the University of Nebraska at Omaha, graduating with a degree in Business Administration. Steve significant experience in business has enabled him to take on national and local leadership roles in both the nonprofit and academic worlds as well.  He currently serves as the Audit Committee Chair for the National Board of Trustees of the March of Dimes, as well as serving on their National Volunteer Leadership Counsel.  He served two terms as the Chairman of the Board for the Nebraska Chapter and was voted the Volunteer of the year twice.  Steve served on the Board of Directors for the American Heart Association in Nebraska, where he was voted Volunteer of the Year in 1992.  He was a member of the First Capital Partners Advisory Board, a mid-market mezzanine finance firm in Omaha, the Iowa West Foundation Investment Committee, and served on the Omaha Community Partnership Board as well.  Steve was a member of Vistage International from 2013 – 2016, an international CEO mentoring and educational organization. Steve also served as an adjunct professor in the Executive MBA program for his alma mater.  His students, funded by a $1 million grant from First National Bank, managed a fixed income portfolio as part of their curriculum through the 2007-2009 financial crisis.  Two years in a row, his classes competed in and won the prestigious Dayton University competition, earning first place for risk adjusted performance. Steve has made several appearances on CNBC and Bloomberg TV and been quoted multiple times by the Wall Street Journal and the Omaha World Herald.  Steve is a sought-after speaker, having given over 100 speeches on various investment and economic related issues over his three-decade career.

description: Meet Our Team DON FULLER Associate Broker / Manager Don has been a real estate broker for over 40 years, serving the greater Omaha area and surrounding communities. As group leader, Don brings many years of knowledge and first-hand experience to his team. His resume includes real estate sales and development, owner/partnership in several real estate-related businesses, and new home construction - building over 500 homes in the Omaha area. Achieving designations such CRS, GRI and Graduate of Builders Institute, as well as his broad experience in finance and marketing have contributed to making Don one of the top producing agents in the city of Omaha. Attending national real estate conferences and focusing on the latest technology and innovations in marketing are only some of the ways Don continues his “commitment to excellence”. Over the years Don has mentored some of Omaha’s finest agents. He believes in giving back to the community, helping others attain their goals and building life-long friendships along the way. JAN FULLER Licensed Realtor® HSR Certified Home Stager & Redesigner A licensed realtor in the Omaha Fuller Group, Jan also brings another significant benefit to the group. She has been a certified professional home stager/re-designer in the Omaha area for many years. With staged properties selling 50% faster and up to 30% more, Jan brings her staging services and knowledge as a complimentary service to all Omaha Fuller Group listings. With a history in the new construction industry, Jan enjoys exercising her decorating talents by making new construction home selections for models and spec homes for builders in the Omaha area, as well as guiding clients through the selection process. Her staging experience also carries over into this area by staging and furnishing model homes. “When you love what you do, you’ll never have to work a day in your life”. And Jan loves what she does! CORY FULLER Licensed Realtor® I have been a licensed Realtor in Nebraska since 2004, have sold over $100 Million in residential real estate and have been previously ranked in the top 15% of all Realtors in the nation.  I have an absolute passion for helping both home buyers and sellers reach their goal of moving on to the next step of their lives.  Working with clients in ALL price ranges, whether it be a $100K or $800K home, each transaction receives equal importance. I am here to make the process simple, smooth and enjoyable and utilize the latest in technology on all fronts to make it happen. I also believe strongly in giving back to our community. It was my privilege to be involved in raising money for The Sunshine Kids Foundation, a wonderful organization who's sole focus is giving kids who are battling cancer every day, the childhood memories they deserve through trips, events and activities nationwide with other kids who have similar challenges.  I have raised over $90,000 for this organization, by sponsoring a huge annual fundraiser called Marchi Gras, a two night live music festival, at which all of the proceeds have gone to The Sunshine Kids Foundation. JASON FULLER Photographer Technology Consultant Owner of Lifestyle 360, Jason is a member of Professional Photographers of America and was certified as a Google Street View Trusted Photographer in January of 2018. He has a diverse background in photography; graphics, web, and UI/Ux design; video production; music arrangements and performance; and collaboration science. Jason has always had a passion for technology and photography and obtained his Master's degree in 2009 from the college of Information Systems and Quantitative Analysis at the University of Nebraska.

description: Melissa Gerdes, a seasoned professional with two decades of experience in the social work industry, embarked on a new chapter by leveraging her passion for real estate. After acquiring her Nebraska real estate license, Melissa's journey in the Omaha market has been defined by her unwavering commitment to client satisfaction. Known for treating clients like family, Melissa's approach is characterized by friendliness, openness, and compassion. Clients appreciate her accessibility and the assurance that their needs will always take precedence. Melissa's reputation for integrity is a cornerstone in guiding clients through the complexities of property transactions, instilling trust in every step of the buying or selling process. Melissa's extensive professional network proves invaluable for clients, whether navigating challenging loans, connecting with reliable remodeling teams, or finding the ideal commercial location. Beyond conventional real estate services, Melissa goes the extra mile by covering professional cleaning and moving expenses, as well as providing complimentary staging services to alleviate the stresses of the real estate journey. Recognizing the transformative impact of a dedicated real estate agent, Melissa draws on her years of property transactions to simplify the process for her clients. Her commitment is reflected not only in professional endeavors but also in personal touches, ensuring each client receives the attention and care she would expect from her own real estate agent. A native of California, Melissa now calls Omaha home, residing with her exceptional and talented children. Fluent in both English and Spanish, Melissa's multicultural proficiency enhances her ability to connect with a diverse clientele. Embracing the local lifestyle, she finds joy in reading, decorating, gardening, baking, and exploring new destinations with her family. Her love for the Omaha community and its offerings resonates in every aspect of her life, both personally and professionally.

description: Shawn is the owner of Foundry Home Realty Group, LLC and a co-owner and principal designer at Foundry Home Interior Design, Inc.  Shawn has a Master of Science in Architecture with a Specialization in Interior Design from the University of Nebraska – Lincoln as well as undergraduate degrees in Art History and Interior Design. Staying ahead of the curve as an innovator, change maker, top producer & trend setter, Shawn is committed to bringing fresh ideas to the marketplace.  Her passion, talent & expertise has gained her numerous accolades in the industry acquired in over 20 years of experience in the business.  She is an expert in all aspects of real estate and design from ideation to valuation. “Real Estate, new construction, remodeling & interior design are challenging and equally fulfilling lines of work.  Being a professional real estate agent and interior designer is both fascinating & rewarding.  It is such an honor to be able to use my knowledge, skill & talent to positively impact peoples’ lives and add value.” Shawn’s interests include global interior dynamics, evidence-based design, the history of interior furnishings, material culture & the demonstrated positive economic impact interior design has on new construction real estate values. Remaining active in the community with civic and charity events is important to Shawn.  Her design was featured in the KETV Channel 7 Showcase Home (proceeds from the tickets sales for this home tour went to Angels Among Us).  Shawn also supports the Sunshine Kids Charity & the Ronald McDonald House.  Her time outside of work is spent with her family & friends, visiting art galleries, listening to live music & traveling.

description: Kathy has been a licensed real estate agent for more than 20 years now. Many of those years were spent as a Domestic and International Corporate Relocation specialist. As a well-connected professional within the Omaha business community, she has her finger on the pulse of local corporations. Kathy is truly at her best when there are multiple balls in the air and she can alleviate stress for her client, helping them make clear decisions. With a father who was a farmer and mother who was a schoolteacher, she learned what grit, perseverance and hard work were at a very early age. Not many realtors take on the roles of organizer, stager, photographer, handyman, therapist, housekeeper, painter, tour guide, savvy marketer and keen negotiator, but Kathy does it all. Give her the challenge and she will bring you the result. "I consistently surprise people with an innate ability to make good things happen. I pay attention to every detail and will stand behind you every step of the way, developing a relationship of trust through knowledge, patience and good humor. I ensure that the process of negotiating the logistical, emotional and financial hurdles of your transaction will be made as easy as possible." – Kathy Lanphier

Now I have a small team of realtors that work with me, and together we have a very well rounded group. From first time home buyers, to seasoned investors, land to commercial, we have the background to help you meet your real estate goals! description: “There’s no place more important than home.” Christie Oberto believes this so strongly that she’s built her entire life around it. Although she’s traveled the world, she’s chosen to raise her family in the same Regency neighborhood where she grew up. And, whether it’s buying or selling, she goes above and beyond to help other families achieve their home goals as well. Christie elevates every stage of the real estate process with her warm, responsive professionalism and comprehensive, first-hand knowledge of the Omaha home market. Because Christie’s clients are often her neighbors—or referred to by her neighbors—she’s truly able to keep her finger on the pulse of what’s happening in the local market, and be a valued resource at every stage of the real estate process: from buying to renovating to selling. She understands that every home decision is part of a big-picture strategy. She has a strong sense of responsibility in being entrusted to guide her clients with her expertise and first-hand knowledge of Omaha real estate. As an Omaha native, a strong supporter of and volunteer with local charitable organizations and a mother of two school-aged children, Christie is invested in Omaha for life. She loves being the go-to when her clients have questions about anything— from ways to add value to your home or who to call for repairs, to fun local places to meet up with friends. “I find joy in the relationships, not just the transaction. I would rather exceed a client’s expectations and establish long-term rapport and trust rather than close a sale that may not be right.”

description: Meet Ria Ria is a real estate broker with over 12 years of experience in multiple markets. She started her career by working with investors and asset management firms in the Philadelphia area. After becoming greatly knowledgeable in the field, she challenged herself to restart her career by moving to San Francisco. During her time there, she gained the valuable skills needed to thrive in a fast moving market. Equipped with extensive experience and sales strategies, Ria moved to the Scottsdale market to coach and develop 45+ agents.  Ria had the opportunity to build her own home in Omaha - her husband’s native city. Surrounded by family, Ria is thrilled to call Omaha her new home. Having been on both sides of the home buying process as a buyer and seller, Ria prides herself on providing unparalleled service to each client through her perseverance, integrity, empathy, and attention. While knowing that buying a home is a unique, important, and emotional process, Ria is eager to guide you in getting your dream home.

description: Get to Know Ann & Kathy Whether you're working directly with Ann or Kathy, you'll always have access to both. That's because, while they each have different experiences and skillsets, they work together and share a common goal of making sure their clients have the best buying and selling experiences possible. Every time. Making Moves Happen in the Community for More Than 25 Years Serving Omaha, Elkhorn, Bellevue, Bennington, Gretna, La Vista, Papillion, Ralston and more! Two is Better Than One What makes us different from other real estate agents? Other than the fact that we truly do go above and beyond in all aspects of our job? (And, no, we're not afraid to say that.) With us, you're basically getting two for one. While you have one point of contact, you also have access to both of us and our strengths. What are those exactly? Read below and we'll tell you all about our professional experience, our points of expertise, and even a few of our favorite things. Ann Townsend Ann.Townsend@bhhsamb.com 402.706.3037 Residential Investment Specialist MRP (Military Referral Program) As part of a relocated family, Ann has the first-hand experience with all the emotions, stress and logistics of moving a household, family and life to a new city. With a father who is a disabled veteran, transitioning military families in and out of our community is her sweet spot. Ann and her husband used to own a real estate portfolio of 48 units until she decided to go into residential real estate in 2011. Now, with a real estate background, relocation experience, an accounting degree and community involvement, Ann is able to sell Omaha, find the right house and ensure her clients get the best prices for the house they are buying or selling. Ann uses all the tools available to ensure her clients get into their dream homes. Known for her honesty, integrity and dedication, Kathy always has the best interest of her buyers and sellers at heart. Ann works with the Omaha Chamber of Commerce, Omaha Children’s Hospital, Creighton University HCOB, ABIDE, Catholic Charities, JDRF and Little White Dog Rescue "I am an agent you can trust to be at your side during the entire home-buying process. Exceeding expectations, responsive communication and personal customer service are hallmarks of my business. This high-level of service is what you can expect to receive as I use all tools available to ensure you end up in your dream home. Because you MATTER, I am always on your side." – Ann Townsend Kathy Lanphier kathy.lanphier@bhhsamb.com 402.670.1040 Corporate Relocation Specialist Kathy has been a licensed real estate agent for more than 20 years now. Many of those years were spent as a Domestic and International Corporate Relocation specialist. As a well-connected professional within the Omaha business community, she has her finger on the pulse of local corporations. Kathy is truly at her best when there are multiple balls in the air and she can alleviate stress for her client, helping them make clear decisions. With a father who was a farmer and mother who was a schoolteacher, she learned what grit, perseverance and hard work were at a very early age. Not many realtors take on the roles of organizer, stager, photographer, handyman, therapist, housekeeper, painter, tour guide, savvy marketer and keen negotiator, but Kathy does it all. Give her the challenge and she will bring you the result. "I consistently surprise people with an innate ability to make good things happen. I pay attention to every detail and will stand behind you every step of the way, developing a relationship of trust through knowledge, patience and good humor. I ensure that the process of negotiating the logistical, emotional and financial hurdles of your transaction will be made as easy as possible." – Kathy Lanphier
